snippet.textDisplay:
“I know that everyone relates this song to Sohni Mahiwal, but for me its meaning is more spiritual.
It kind of has two meanings, and that is why it’s beautiful.
For example, ‘kacchi Meri mitti, kachyan te rakhyiye na umeed par di’ means that we should place our trust only in Allah in every situation.”
